{"title_page": "Pousada de Saramagos", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name = Pousada de Saramagos\n|image_shield = coat_of_arms_pousada_de_saramagos.jpg\n|region             = [[Norte Region, Portugal|Norte]]\n|CIM                = [[Ave (intermunicipal community)|Ave]]\n|district           = [[Braga District|Braga]]\n|municipality       = [[Vila Nova de Famalic\u00e3o]]\n|area_total = 2.12\n|population_total = 2234\n|population_as_of = 2011\n|coordinates   = {{coord|41.4292|-8.4333|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|website = http://jf-pousada-saramagos.com/\n|footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''Pousada de Saramagos''' is a Portuguese village belonging to the municipality of [[Vila Nova de Famalic\u00e3o]], in the North of Portugal, more precisely in the region of [[Minho Province|Minho]]. The population in 2011 was 2,234,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 2.12&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>[http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ \u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds]</ref> It is about 9&nbsp;km far from its municipal seat.<ref>{{cite web   | title = Historial   | url = http://jf-pousada-saramagos.com/   | accessdate = 24 August 2009   | url-status = dead   | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090814102837/http://jf-pousada-saramagos.com/   | archivedate = 14 August 2009   }}</ref>\n\n==History==\nSince Pousada de Saramagos is located in one of the most ancient parts of Portugal, its history is very rich and it's also connected to the early evidence of the existence of Pousada de Saramagos can be found in texts dated of 1076, actually predating both the year of the ''de facto'' recognition of [[Portugal]] as a country and the papal bull issued by the pope to recognize it as a Christian country.\n\n==Geography==\nPousada de Saramagos is located in the [[Minho Province|Minho]] region of [[Portugal]], halfway between Vila Nova de Famalic\u00e3o and [[Guimar\u00e3es]]. It belongs to the municipality of [[Vila Nova de Famalic\u00e3o]] and its district capital is [[Braga]].\n\n==Population==\nSince the national census in 2001, the population of the parish grew more than 35%, to house more 784 inhabitants. Part of it is due to the building of houses in the north of the village, mainly ''Parque dos Loureiros''.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Parishes of Vila Nova de Famalic\u00e3o]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name = Pousada de Saramagos\n|image_shield = coat_of_arms_pousada_de_saramagos.jpg\n|region             = [[Norte Region, Portugal|Norte]]\n|CIM                = [[Ave (intermunicipal community)|Ave]]\n|district           = [[Braga District|Braga]]\n|municipality       = [[Vila Nova de Famalic\u00e3o]]\n|area_total = 2.12\n|population_total = 2234\n|population_as_of = 2011\n|coordinates   = {{coord|41.4292|-8.4333|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|website = http://jf-pousada-saramagos.com/\n|footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''Pousada de Saramagos''' is a Portuguese village belonging to the municipality of [[Vila Nova de Famalic\u00e3o]], in the North of Portugal, more precisely in the region of [[Minho Province|Minho]]. The population in 2011 was 2,234,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 2.12&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>[http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ \u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds]</ref> It is about 9&nbsp;km far from its municipal seat.<ref>{{cite web   | title = Historial   | url = http://jf-pousada-saramagos.com/   | accessdate = 24 August 2009   | url-status = dead   | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090814102837/http://jf-pousada-saramagos.com/   | archivedate = 14 August 2009   }}</ref>\n\n==History==\nSince Pousada de Saramagos is located in one of the most ancient parts of Portugal, its history is very rich and it's also connected to the early evidence of the existence of Pousada de Saramagos can be found in texts dated of 1076, actually predating both the year of the ''de facto'' recognition of [[Portugal]] as a country and the papal bull issued by the pope to recognize it as a Christian country.\n\n==Geography==\nPousada de Saramagos is located in the [[Minho Province|Minho]] region of [[Portugal]], halfway between Vila Nova de Famalic\u00e3o and [[Guimar\u00e3es]]. It belongs to the municipality of [[Vila Nova de Famalic\u00e3o]] and its district capital is [[Braga]].\n\n==Population==\nSince the national census in 2001, the population of the parish grew more than 35%, to house more 784 inhabitants. Part of it is due to the building of houses in the north of the village, mainly ''Parque dos Loureiros''.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Parishes of Vila Nova de Famalic\u00e3o]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pousada_de_Saramagos"}
{"title_page": "Pousa", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name = Pousa\n|image_shield =\n|region             = Norte\n|CIM                = [[C\u00e1vado (intermunicipal community)|C\u00e1vado]]\n|district           = [[Braga District|Braga]]\n|municipality       = [[Barcelos, Portugal|Barcelos]]\n|area_total = 6.63\n|population_total = 2272\n|population_as_of = 2011\n|coordinates   = {{coord|41.552|-8.518|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|website = \n|footnotes =\n}}\n'''Pousa''' is a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] ''[[freguesia]]'' (\"civil parish\"), located in the municipality of [[Barcelos Municipality, Portugal|Barcelos]]. The population in 2011 was 2,272,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 6.63&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>[http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ \u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds]</ref>\n\n[[Image:Capela Nossa Senhora da Esperanca - Pousa.jpg|left|thumb|Our Lady of Hope Chapel]]\n\nPousa is located in between the two sub-cities (Barcelos and Braga) in the northern region of Portugal. Many of its residents work in the sub-cities as they are within 30 minutes reach using motorised transport. It is surrounded by a beautiful mainstream river along with mountains filled with pine/oak trees. Forest fires are rare but not overlooked by authorities as there is at least one every year. Pousa has the ''Auto Estrada Porto-Valen\u00e7a'' running across through its border of its neighbour (Graca).\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Parishes of Barcelos}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Parishes of Barcelos, Portugal]]\n\n\n{{braga-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name = Pousa\n|image_shield =\n|region             = Norte\n|CIM                = [[C\u00e1vado (intermunicipal community)|C\u00e1vado]]\n|district           = [[Braga District|Braga]]\n|municipality       = [[Barcelos, Portugal|Barcelos]]\n|area_total = 6.63\n|population_total = 2272\n|population_as_of = 2011\n|coordinates   = {{coord|41.552|-8.518|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|website = \n|footnotes =\n}}\n'''Pousa''' is a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] ''[[freguesia]]'' (\"civil parish\"), located in the municipality of [[Barcelos Municipality, Portugal|Barcelos]]. The population in 2011 was 2,272,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 6.63&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>[http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ \u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds]</ref>\n\n[[Image:Capela Nossa Senhora da Esperanca - Pousa.jpg|left|thumb|Our Lady of Hope Chapel]]\n\nPousa is located in between the two sub-cities (Barcelos and Braga) in the northern region of Portugal. Many of its residents work in the sub-cities as they are within 30 minutes reach using motorised transport. It is surrounded by a beautiful mainstream river along with mountains filled with pine/oak trees. Forest fires are rare but not overlooked by authorities as there is at least one every year. Pousa has the ''Auto Estrada Porto-Valen\u00e7a'' running across through its border of its neighbour (Graca).\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Parishes of Barcelos}}\n\n[[Category:Parishes of Barcelos, Portugal]]\n\n\n{{braga-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pousa"}
{"title_page": "Posto Santo", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision\n| type                    = parish\n| name                    = Posto Santo\n| image_skyline           = Caldeira guilherme moniz2.jpg\n| image_caption           = The crater face of the Guilherme Moniz caldera, on the eastern edge of the parish's frontier\n| region                  = Azores\n| island                  = [[Terceira Island|Terceira]]\n| municipality            = [[Angra do Hero\u00edsmo]]\n| coordinates             = {{coord|38|40|42|N|27|13|51|W|display=inline,title}}\n| established_date        = Settlement: fl. 1500<br>Parish: fl. 1599<br>Civil parish: 15 September 1980\n| area_total_km2          = 20.37\n| elevation_m             = 211\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_total        = 1048\n| postal_code             = 9700-238\n| area_code               = (+351) 292 XXX-XXXX\n| website                 = {{url|http://www.jfpostosanto.pt}}\n}}\n'''Posto Santo''' is a parish in the municipality of [[Angra do Hero\u00edsmo]] on the island of [[Terceira Island|Terceira]] in the [[Azores]]. The population in 2011 was 1,048,<ref>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 20.37&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref>[http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/portal/page/portal/nuts_nomenclature/documents/PT-LAU.xls Eurostat]</ref> Posto Santo was elevated to parish status on 15 September 1980. It was previously part of the parish of [[Santa Luzia (Angra do Hero\u00edsmo)|Santa Luzia]]. The parish is relatively far from the ocean, and it lies at an elevation of forty-five metres. Its predominant economic activity is agriculture. It contains the localities Espig\u00e3o, Grota do Medo, Lapinha, Piquinho and Posto Santo.\n\n==History==\nThe name, ''\"Posto Santo\"'', is literally translated as ''\"holy post\"'', its origin developed from an outbreak of bubonic plague in 1599 that killed thousands on the island of Terceira. The parish of Posto Santo was spared and served as a refuge for many of the residents of Angra do Hero\u00edsmo. Since then, it has been known as Posto Santo.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Angra do Hero\u00edsmo}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Parishes of Angra do Hero\u00edsmo]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision\n| type                    = parish\n| name                    = Posto Santo\n| image_skyline           = Caldeira guilherme moniz2.jpg\n| image_caption           = The crater face of the Guilherme Moniz caldera, on the eastern edge of the parish's frontier\n| region                  = Azores\n| island                  = [[Terceira Island|Terceira]]\n| municipality            = [[Angra do Hero\u00edsmo]]\n| coordinates             = {{coord|38|40|42|N|27|13|51|W|display=inline,title}}\n| established_date        = Settlement: fl. 1500<br>Parish: fl. 1599<br>Civil parish: 15 September 1980\n| area_total_km2          = 20.37\n| elevation_m             = 211\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_total        = 1048\n| postal_code             = 9700-238\n| area_code               = (+351) 292 XXX-XXXX\n| website                 = {{url|http://www.jfpostosanto.pt}}\n}}\n'''Posto Santo''' is a parish in the municipality of [[Angra do Hero\u00edsmo]] on the island of [[Terceira Island|Terceira]] in the [[Azores]]. The population in 2011 was 1,048,<ref>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 20.37&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref>[http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/portal/page/portal/nuts_nomenclature/documents/PT-LAU.xls Eurostat]</ref> Posto Santo was elevated to parish status on 15 September 1980. It was previously part of the parish of [[Santa Luzia (Angra do Hero\u00edsmo)|Santa Luzia]]. The parish is relatively far from the ocean, and it lies at an elevation of forty-five metres. Its predominant economic activity is agriculture. It contains the localities Espig\u00e3o, Grota do Medo, Lapinha, Piquinho and Posto Santo.\n\n==History==\nThe name, ''\"Posto Santo\"'', is literally translated as ''\"holy post\"'', its origin developed from an outbreak of bubonic plague in 1599 that killed thousands on the island of Terceira. The parish of Posto Santo was spared and served as a refuge for many of the residents of Angra do Hero\u00edsmo. Since then, it has been known as Posto Santo.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Angra do Hero\u00edsmo}}\n\n[[Category:Parishes of Angra do Hero\u00edsmo]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Posto_Santo"}
